params.name: field

functions.name: getLastElement

functions.name: randomString

functions.name: checkLength

functions.name: chunk

returns.description: Returns the new array of chunks

functions.name: compact
functions.description: Creates an array with all falsy values removed

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: concat
functions.description: Creates a new array concatenating array with any additional arrays and/or values

functions.name: difference

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: differenceBy

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: differenceWith

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: drop
functions.description: Creates a slice of array with n elements dropped from the beginning

params.name: n
params.description: =1] - The number of elements to drop

functions.name: dropRight
functions.description: Creates a slice of array with n elements dropped from the end

params.name: n
params.description: =1] - The number of elements to drop

functions.name: dropWhile
functions.description: Creates a slice of array excluding elements dropped from the beginning

functions.name: dropRightWhile
functions.description: Creates a slice of array excluding elements dropped from the end

functions.name: fill
functions.description: Fills elements of array with value from start up to, but not including, end

params.name: value
params.description: The value to fill array with

functions.name: findIndex

params.name: predicate
params.type: (value: T, index: number, array: T[]) => boolean

returns.description: Returns the index of the found element, else -1

functions.name: findLastIndex
functions.description: Like findIndex except that it iterates over elements from right to left

params.name: predicate
params.type: (value: T, index: number, array: T[]) => boolean

returns.description: Returns the index of the found element, else -1

functions.name: flatten
functions.description: Flattens array a single level deep

functions.name: flattenDeep
functions.description: Recursively flattens array

functions.name: flattenDepth
functions.description: Recursively flatten array up to depth times

functions.name: reverse
functions.description: Reverses array so that the first element becomes the last

functions.name: union
functions.description: Creates an array of unique values from all given arrays

returns.description: Returns the new array of combined values

functions.name: unionBy
functions.description: Like union except that it accepts iteratee

returns.description: Returns the new array of combined values

functions.name: intersection
functions.description: Creates an array of unique values that are included in all given arrays

returns.description: Returns the new array of intersecting values

functions.name: intersectionBy
functions.description: Like intersection except that it accepts iteratee

returns.description: Returns the new array of intersecting values

functions.name: pull
functions.description: Removes all given values from array

returns.description: Returns the new array with values removed

functions.name: pullAt
functions.description: Removes elements from array corresponding to indexes

params.name: indexes
params.description: The indexes of elements to remove

returns.description: Returns the new array with elements removed

functions.name: remove
functions.description: Removes all elements from array that predicate returns truthy for

params.name: predicate
params.type: (value: T, index: number, array: T[]) => boolean

returns.description: Returns an array of removed elements

functions.example:
const array = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const evens = remove(array, n => n % 2 === 0); // evens: [2, 4], array: [1, 3]

functions.name: tail
functions.description: Gets all but the first element of array

functions.name: take
functions.description: Creates a slice of array with n elements taken from the beginning

params.name: n
params.description: =1] - The number of elements to take

functions.name: takeRight
functions.description: Creates a slice of array with n elements taken from the end

params.name: n
params.description: =1] - The number of elements to take

functions.name: takeWhile
functions.description: Creates a slice of array with elements taken from the beginning

functions.name: takeRightWhile
functions.description: Creates a slice of array with elements taken from the end

functions.name: without
functions.description: Creates an array of unique values from the first array not included in the other given arrays

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: xor
functions.description: Creates an array of unique values that is the symmetric difference of the given arrays

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: zip
functions.description: Creates an array that is the zip of arrays

returns.description: Returns the new array of grouped elements

functions.name: zipObject
functions.description: Creates an object composed from arrays of keys and values

functions.name: zipWith
functions.description: Creates an array of grouped elements

params.name: arrays
params.description: The arrays to process and the function to combine grouped values

returns.description: Returns the new array of grouped elements

functions.name: unzip
functions.description: The opposite of zip; creates an array of arrays

params.name: array
params.description: The array of grouped elements to process

returns.description: Returns the new array of regrouped elements

functions.name: head
functions.description: Gets the first element of array

returns.description: Returns the first element of array

functions.name: last
functions.description: Gets the last element of array

returns.description: Returns the last element of array

functions.name: nth
functions.description: Gets the element at index n of array

params.name: n
params.description: =0] - The index of the element to return

returns.description: Returns the nth element of array

functions.name: initial
functions.description: Gets all but the last element of array

functions.name: unionWith
functions.description: Creates an array of unique values from all given arrays using SameValueZero for equality comparisons

returns.description: Returns the new array of combined values

functions.name: intersectionWith
functions.description: Creates an array of unique values that are included in all given arrays using SameValueZero for equality comparisons

returns.description: Returns the new array of intersecting values

functions.name: xorWith
functions.description: Like xor except that it accepts comparator which is invoked to compare elements

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: xorBy
functions.description: Like xor except that it accepts iteratee which is invoked for each element

returns.description: Returns the new array of filtered values

functions.name: zipObjectDeep
functions.description: Like zipObject except that it supports property paths

functions.name: pullAll
functions.description: Creates an array of elements corresponding to the given keys

returns.description: Returns the new array with values removed

functions.name: pullAllBy
functions.description: Like pullAll except that it accepts iteratee which is invoked per element

returns.description: Returns the new array with values removed

functions.name: pullAllWith
functions.description: Like pullAll except that it accepts comparator which is invoked to compare elements

returns.description: Returns the new array with values removed

functions.name: uniq
functions.description: Creates a duplicate-free version of an array using SameValueZero for equality comparisons

returns.description: Returns the new duplicate free array

functions.name: uniqBy
functions.description: Like uniq except that it accepts iteratee which is invoked for each element

returns.description: Returns the new duplicate free array

functions.name: uniqWith
functions.description: Like uniq except that it accepts comparator which is invoked to compare elements

returns.description: Returns the new duplicate free array

functions.name: unzipWith
functions.description: Creates an array excluding all given values using SameValueZero for equality comparisons

params.name: array
params.description: The array of grouped elements to process

params.name: iteratee
params.description: The function to combine regrouped values

returns.description: Returns the new array of regrouped elements

functions.name: sortedIndex
functions.description: Creates an array of elements sorted in ascending order

returns.description: Returns the index at which value should be inserted into array

functions.name: sortedIndexBy
functions.description: Like sortedIndex except that it accepts iteratee

returns.description: Returns the index at which value should be inserted into array

functions.name: sortedLastIndex
functions.description: Uses a binary search to determine the highest index at which value should be inserted

returns.description: Returns the index at which value should be inserted into array

functions.name: sortedLastIndexBy
functions.description: Like sortedLastIndex except that it accepts iteratee

returns.description: Returns the index at which value should be inserted into array

functions.name: sortedIndexOf
functions.description: Uses a binary search to find the index of the value in the sorted array

returns.description: Returns the index of the matched value, else -1

functions.name: sortedLastIndexOf
functions.description: Uses a binary search to find the last index of the value in the sorted array

returns.description: Returns the index of the matched value, else -1

functions.name: slice
functions.description: Creates a slice of array from start up to, but not including, end

functions.name: join
functions.description: Joins a list of elements using a separator

functions.name: indexOf
functions.description: Gets the index at which the first occurrence of value is found in array

returns.description: Returns the index of the matched value, else -1

functions.name: lastIndexOf
functions.description: Gets the index at which the last occurrence of value is found in array

returns.description: Returns the index of the matched value, else -1

functions.name: filterData
functions.description: Filters an array of objects based on provided parameters

params.name: arr
params.description: The array of objects to be filtered

returns.description: Returns the filtered array containing objects of type T

functions.name: every
functions.description: Checks if predicate returns truthy for all elements of collection.

functions.name: forEach
functions.description: Iterates over elements of collection and invokes iteratee for each element.
functions.example:
forEach([1, 2], value => console.log(value))
forEach({a: 1, b: 2}, (value, key) => console.log(key, value))

functions.name: map
functions.description: Creates an array of values by running each element in collection through iteratee.

functions.name: filter
functions.description: Iterates over elements of collection, returning an array of all elements predicate returns truthy for.

functions.name: find
functions.description: Iterates over elements of collection, returning the first element predicate returns truthy for.

functions.name: findKey
functions.description: This method is like find except that it returns the key of the first element

functions.name: findLast
functions.description: This method is like find except that it iterates over elements of collection from right to left.

functions.name: flatMap
functions.description: Creates a flattened array of values by running each element in collection through iteratee

functions.name: flatMapDeep
functions.description: This method is like flatMap except that it recursively flattens the mapped results.

functions.name: groupBy
functions.description: Creates an object composed of keys generated from the results of running each element

functions.name: includes
functions.description: Checks if value is in collection. If collection is a string, it's checked for a substring of value,
functions.example:
includes([1, 2, 3], 1) // => true
includes({a: 1, b: 2}, 1) // => true
includes('hello', 'ell') // => true

functions.name: invokeMap
functions.description: Invokes the method at path of each element in collection, returning an array of the results

functions.name: keyBy
functions.description: Creates an object composed of keys generated from the results of running each element
functions.example:
keyBy([{id: 'a', dir: 'left'}, {id: 'b', dir: 'right'}], x => x.id) 
// => {a: {id: 'a', dir: 'left'}, b: {id: 'b', dir: 'right'}}

functions.name: orderBy
functions.description: Creates an array of elements, sorted in ascending or descending order by the results

functions.name: partition
functions.description: Creates an array of elements split into two groups, the first of which contains elements

functions.name: reduce
functions.description: Reduces collection to a value which is the accumulated result of running each element
functions.example:
reduce([1, 2], (sum, n) => sum + n, 0) // => 3
reduce({a: 1, b: 2, c: 1}, (result, value, key) => { ... }, {})

functions.name: reduceRight
functions.description: This method is like reduce except that it iterates over elements of collection from right to left.

functions.name: reject
functions.description: The opposite of filter; this method returns the elements of collection that predicate

functions.name: sample
functions.description: Gets a random element from collection.

functions.name: sampleSize
functions.description: Gets n random elements at unique keys from collection up to the size of collection.

functions.name: shuffle
functions.description: Creates an array of shuffled values, using a version of the Fisher-Yates shuffle.

functions.name: size
functions.description: Gets the size of collection by returning its length for array-like values or the number

functions.name: some
functions.description: Checks if predicate returns truthy for any element of collection. Iteration is stopped
functions.example:
some([null, 0, 'yes', false], Boolean) // => true
some({a: null, b: 0, c: 'yes'}, Boolean) // => true

functions.name: sortBy
functions.description: Creates an array of elements, sorted in ascending order by the results of running
functions.example:
sortBy([{user: 'fred', age: 48}, {user: 'barney', age: 36}], x => x.age)
// => [{user: 'barney', age: 36}, {user: 'fred', age: 48}]

functions.name: countBy
functions.description: Creates an object composed of keys generated from the results of running each element

functions.name: eachRight
functions.description: This method is like forEach except that it iterates over elements of collection from right to left.

functions.name: forEachRight
functions.description: Alias for eachRight. This method is like forEach except that it iterates over elements

functions.name: formatDate
functions.description: Format a date to string using a custom format pattern

functions.name: isDate
functions.description: Check if a value is a valid Date object
functions.example:
```typescript
isDate(new Date()) // true
isDate('2023-12-25') // false (string, not Date object)
isDate(new Date('invalid')) // false (invalid date)
```

functions.name: now
functions.description: Get the current date and time, optionally formatted
functions.example:
```typescript
now() // Date object for current time
now('DD/MM/YYYY HH:mm') // '25/12/2023 14:30'
```

functions.name: secondsToTomorrow
functions.description: Calculate the number of seconds remaining until tomorrow (midnight)
functions.example:
```typescript
// If current time is 23:30:00
secondsToTomorrow() // 1800 (30 minutes = 1800 seconds)
```

functions.name: isDateDifferent
functions.description: Check if a given number differs from the current time's corresponding unit
functions.example:
```typescript
// If current time is 14:30:45 on 25th December 2023
isDateDifferent(15, 'hour') // true (current hour is 14)
isDateDifferent(30, 'minute') // false (current minute is 30)
isDateDifferent(2023, 'year') // false (current year is 2023)
```

functions.name: getFormat
functions.description: Get the date/time format string for a specific country and format type

functions.name: isBetween
functions.description: Check if a date falls between two other dates (inclusive)

functions.name: addTime
functions.description: Add a specified amount of time to a date
functions.example:
```typescript
addTime(new Date('2023-12-25'), 5, 'day') // 2023-12-30
addTime('2023-12-25T10:00:00', 2, 'hour') // 2023-12-25T12:00:00
addTime(new Date(), -1, 'month') // One month ago
addTime('2023-01-31', 1, 'month') // 2023-02-28 (handles month overflow)
```

functions.name: bind
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes func with the this binding of thisArg and arguments of the created function

functions.name: bindKey
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes the method at object[key] with arguments

functions.name: ary
functions.description: Creates a function that accepts up to n arguments, ignoring any additional arguments

functions.name: flip
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes func with arguments reversed

functions.name: memoize
functions.description: Creates a function that memoizes the result of func

functions.name: negate
functions.description: Creates a function that negates the result of the predicate func

functions.name: once
functions.description: Creates a function that is restricted to invoking func once

functions.name: overArgs
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes func with its arguments transformed

functions.name: partial
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes func with partials prepended to the arguments it receives

functions.name: partialRight
functions.description: Like partial except that partially applied arguments are appended to the arguments it receives

functions.name: rearg
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes func with arguments arranged according to the specified indexes

functions.name: spread
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes func with the this binding of the created function and an array of arguments

functions.name: throttle
functions.description: Creates a throttled function that only invokes func at most once per every wait milliseconds

functions.name: debounce
functions.description: Creates a debounced function that delays invoking func until after wait milliseconds have elapsed

functions.name: unary
functions.description: Creates a function that accepts up to one argument, ignoring any additional arguments

functions.name: wrap
functions.description: Creates a function that provides value to wrapper as its first argument

functions.name: curry
functions.description: Creates a function that accepts arguments of func and either invokes func returning its result,

functions.name: curryRight
functions.description: This method is like curry except that arguments are applied to func in the manner of partialRight instead of partial

functions.name: rest
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes func with arguments arranged according to the specified indexes

functions.name: add
functions.description: Adds two numbers together

functions.name: sum
functions.description: Computes the sum of all values in an array

functions.name: sumBy
functions.description: Computes the sum of all values in an array after applying an iteratee function to each element

functions.name: mean
functions.description: Computes the arithmetic mean (average) of all values in an array

functions.name: meanBy
functions.description: Computes the arithmetic mean of all values in an array after applying an iteratee function

functions.name: max
functions.description: Finds the maximum value in an array of numbers

functions.name: maxBy
functions.description: Finds the element in an array that produces the maximum value when passed through an iteratee function

functions.name: min
functions.description: Finds the minimum value in an array of numbers

functions.name: minBy
functions.description: Finds the element in an array that produces the minimum value when passed through an iteratee function

functions.name: subtract
functions.description: Subtracts the second number from the first number

functions.name: multiply
functions.description: Multiplies two numbers together

functions.name: divide
functions.description: Divides the first number by the second number

functions.name: round
functions.description: Rounds a number to a specified precision

functions.name: ceil
functions.description: Rounds a number up to a specified precision

functions.name: floor
functions.description: Rounds a number down to a specified precision

functions.name: inRange
functions.description: Checks if a number is within a specified range (inclusive start, exclusive end)
functions.example:
```typescript
inRange(3, 2, 4) // => true
inRange(4, 8) // => true (equivalent to inRange(4, 0, 8))
inRange(4, 2) // => false
inRange(2, 2, 4) // => true (start is inclusive)
inRange(4, 2, 4) // => false (end is exclusive)
inRange(1.2, 2, 1) // => true (start and end are swapped automatically)
```

functions.name: std
functions.description: Computes the standard deviation of an array of numbers

functions.name: variance
functions.description: Computes the variance of an array of numbers

functions.name: number
functions.description: Parse string to number if possible

params.name: options
params.description: .deep=false] - Whether to recursively parse nested objects and arrays

returns.description: Parsed number or original value if parsing fails

functions.example:
number('123') // 123
number('abc') // 'abc'
number(['1', '2', 'abc']) // [1, 2, 'abc']
number({ a: '123', b: 'abc' }, { deep: true }) // { a: 123, b: 'abc' }

functions.name: parseFloat
functions.description: Parse float with optional precision

params.name: data
params.description: The data to parse as a floating point number

params.name: precision
params.description: Number of decimal places to round to

returns.description: Parsed float rounded to specified precision, or original value if parsing fails

functions.name: clamp
functions.description: Clamp a number between min and max values

returns.description: The clamped value between min and max

functions.name: random
functions.description: Generate random number between min and max

returns.description: Random floating point number in the specified range

functions.example:
random() // Random number between 0 and 1
random(5, 10) // Random number between 5 and 10

functions.name: randomInt
functions.description: Generate random integer between min and max

returns.description: Random integer in the specified range

functions.example:
randomInt() // Random integer between 0 and 100
randomInt(1, 6) // Random integer between 1 and 6 (like a dice roll)

functions.name: flat
functions.description: Flatten an object and extract values

functions.name: getObjectKeysByType
functions.description: Get object keys by value type

functions.name: getObjectValueByPath
functions.description: Get value from object by path
functions.example:
getObjectValueByPath({ a: { b: { c: 42 } } }, ['a', 'b', 'c']) // 42
getObjectValueByPath({ items: [{ name: 'John' }, { name: 'Jane' }] }, ['items', 'name']) // ['John', 'Jane']

functions.name: isEmpty
functions.description: Check if a value is empty
functions.example:
isEmpty('') // true
isEmpty([]) // true
isEmpty({}) // true
isEmpty({ a: '' }, { props: true }) // true

functions.name: getValueType
functions.description: Gets the type of a value

functions.name: mapValues
functions.description: Creates an object with the same keys as the input object and values generated by running each property through an iteratee function
functions.example:
mapValues({ a: 1, b: 2 }, x => x * 2) // { a: 2, b: 4 }
mapValues({ a: 'hello', b: 'world' }, (value, key) => `${key}: ${value}`) // { a: 'a: hello', b: 'b: world' }

functions.name: mapKeys
functions.description: Creates an object with the same values as the input object and keys generated by running each property through an iteratee function
functions.example: mapKeys({ a: 1, b: 2 }, (value, key) => key.toUpperCase()) // { A: 1, B: 2 }

functions.name: create
functions.description: Creates an object that inherits from the given prototype object
functions.example:
const proto = { greet: () => 'hello' }
const obj = create(proto, { name: 'John' }) // obj.greet() works and obj.name === 'John'

functions.name: assign
functions.description: Assigns own enumerable string keyed properties of source objects to the destination object

functions.name: merge
functions.description: Recursively merges own and inherited enumerable string keyed properties of source objects into the destination object

functions.name: mergeWith
functions.description: Like merge except that it accepts a customizer function which is invoked to produce the merged values
functions.example: mergeWith({ a: [1] }, { a: [2] }, (obj, src) => Array.isArray(obj) ? obj.concat(src) : undefined) // { a: [1, 2] }

functions.name: pick
functions.description: Creates an object composed of the picked object properties

functions.name: pickBy
functions.description: Creates an object composed of properties that satisfy the predicate function
functions.example: pickBy({ a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }, value => value > 1) // { b: 2, c: 3 }

functions.name: omit
functions.description: Creates an object composed of all properties except the specified ones

functions.name: omitBy
functions.description: Creates an object composed of properties that do not satisfy the predicate function
functions.example: omitBy({ a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }, value => value > 1) // { a: 1 }

functions.name: get
functions.description: Gets the value at the specified path of an object

functions.name: set
functions.description: Sets the value at the specified path of an object

functions.name: has
functions.description: Checks if the specified path exists as a direct property of the object
functions.example:
has({ a: { b: { c: 3 } } }, 'a.b.c') // true
has({ a: { b: { c: 3 } } }, 'a.b.d') // false

functions.name: hasIn
functions.description: Checks if the specified path exists as an own property of the object

functions.name: unset
functions.description: Removes the property at the specified path of an object
functions.example:
const obj = { a: { b: { c: 3 } } }
unset(obj, 'a.b.c') // true, obj becomes { a: { b: {} } }

functions.name: keys
functions.description: Creates an array of own enumerable property names of an object

functions.name: values
functions.description: Creates an array of own enumerable property values of an object

functions.name: entries
functions.description: Creates an array of own enumerable string keyed-value pairs for an object

functions.name: entriesIn
functions.description: Creates an array of own and inherited enumerable string keyed-value pairs for an object

functions.name: fromPairs
functions.description: Creates an object from an array of key-value pairs

functions.name: functions
functions.description: Creates an array of function property names from own enumerable properties of an object
functions.example: functions({ a: 1, b: () => {}, c: 'string', d: function() {} }) // ['b', 'd']

functions.name: functionsIn
functions.description: Creates an array of function property names from own and inherited enumerable properties of an object

functions.name: invert
functions.description: Creates an object that inverts the keys and values of the input object

functions.name: invertBy
functions.description: Creates an inverted object where the inverted keys are generated from running each element through an iteratee
functions.example: invertBy({ a: 1, b: 2, c: 1 }, value => `group${value}`) // { group1: ['a', 'c'], group2: ['b'] }

functions.name: transform
functions.description: Transforms an object by running each own enumerable string keyed property through a transform function
functions.example: transform({ a: 1, b: 2 }, (result, value, key) => { result[key] = value * 2 }, {}) // { a: 2, b: 4 }

functions.name: clone
functions.description: Creates a shallow clone of an object
functions.example:
const obj = { a: 1, b: { c: 2 } }
const cloned = clone(obj) // cloned.b === obj.b (same reference)

functions.name: cloneDeep
functions.description: Creates a deep clone of an object
functions.example:
const obj = { a: 1, b: { c: 2 } }
const cloned = cloneDeep(obj) // cloned.b !== obj.b (different reference)

functions.name: isEqual
functions.description: Performs a deep comparison between two values to determine if they are equivalent
functions.example:
isEqual([1, 2, 3], [1, 2, 3]) // true
isEqual({ a: 1 }, { a: 1 }) // true
isEqual({ a: 1 }, { a: 2 }) // false

functions.name: conformsTo
functions.description: Checks if an object conforms to a source by invoking predicate properties with corresponding object values
functions.example: conformsTo({ a: 1, b: 2 }, { a: n => n > 0, b: n => n < 5 }) // true

functions.name: method
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes the method at a specified path of a given object

functions.name: methodOf
functions.description: Creates a function that invokes the method at a given path of the specified object

functions.name: defaults
functions.description: Assigns properties of source objects to the destination object for all destination properties that resolve to undefined

functions.name: defaultsDeep
functions.description: Recursively assigns default properties from source objects to the destination object

functions.name: at
functions.description: Gets the values at multiple paths of an object

functions.name: result
functions.description: Gets the value at path of object. If the resolved value is a function, it's invoked and its result is returned

functions.name: invoke
functions.description: Invokes the method at the specified path of an object

functions.name: update
functions.description: Sets the value at path of object using an updater function

functions.name: updateWith
functions.description: Like update except that it accepts a customizer which is invoked to produce the updated value

functions.name: setWith
functions.description: Like set except that it accepts a customizer which is invoked to produce the objects of path

functions.name: findLastKey
functions.description: Finds the last key of an object where the predicate returns truthy
functions.example: findLastKey({ a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }, n => n > 1) // 'c'

functions.name: forIn
functions.description: Iterates over own and inherited enumerable string keyed properties of an object
functions.example: forIn({ a: 1, b: 2 }, (value, key) => console.log(key, value))

functions.name: forInRight
functions.description: Like forIn except that it iterates over properties in the opposite order
